node.text: Got to catch up with my favorite human @shannonrwatts for a quick tutorial on how to phone bank (a critical step in this phase of the election cycle when we aren’t knocking on doors). You can do this while you watch TV with a glass of wine. And anyone can do it. It’s fun and so easy! we also discuss what you should be watching on tv, important election reminders, and how sleep deprived and delirious we are. Please watch and share! Let’s phone bank!!! 💪☎️ #teamjoetalks @joebiden @votejoe

I #WearOrange today on National Gun Violence Awareness Day to shine a light on the gun violence crisis that takes more than 100 lives and wounds hundreds more every day. We can end gun violence together. 

Orange is the color Hadiya Pendleton’s friends wore in her honor after she was fatally shot in Chicago at age 15 in 2013. After her death, her friends wore orange - the color hunters wear in the woods to protect themselves - to raise awareness about gun violence.

If I could choose one word I hope others would use to describe me, it would be: kind. It was the superlative I got in 8th grade and the superpower I gave my daughters (they wore capes embroidered with The Kindness Kids). Every night as part of our bedtime ritual, we each share one act of kindness we did in our day (along with one thing we are grateful for and someone we want to send extra sweet dreams to). Our daughters are now so excited to model kindness in their days so they can share it with us at night. 

This has become even more important to me as a leader and an executive. I’ve never understood those who choose to lead with fear or lack of compassion. It’s so ineffective and inefficient. 

I am honored to be a part of the @grayson Super campaign, supporting @iamavoter, in my “I am superkind” shirt. Thank you for supporting our organization! #iamavoter
